<paragraph blockId="26.[178,1084,357,409]" pageId="26" pageNumber="1539">
E t y m o l o g y: The trivial name 
<emphasis box="[566,652,357,378]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="1539">subgilva</emphasis>
is a Latin adjective derived from prefix - 
<emphasis box="[178,213,387,408]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="1539">sub</emphasis>
(= less than) and 
<emphasis box="[394,454,387,408]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="1539">gilvus</emphasis>
(= yellow). I refer to the elytral color.
</paragraph>
